climbs.name: Mr. Lizard Meets Flintstone
climbs.fa: Bill Herzog, Rob Mulligan, and Larua Rosa, 1987

content.description: This is a good quality face route, well-protected with bolts.
content.protection: 5 bolts plus gear for an anchor on top
content.location: This is near the left end of the face, but below and right of the downclimb.

climbs.name: Didn't Your Mama Ever Tell You About A Stranger's Bolts
climbs.fa: Rob Mulligan and Bill Odenthal, November 1985

content.description: This is a rather forgettable slab climb.  There is a short crux section on small, somewhat loose flakes, near a bolt.  The rock above the crux is also low quality.
content.protection: 3 bolts plus gear for a belay
content.location: This is a slab route near the left end of the west face.  It is just a bit to the right of Mr. Lizard Meets Flintstone, which is clearly easier and has five bolts.

climbs.name: It Seams Possible
climbs.fa: Bill Odenthal and Rob Mulligan, November 1985

content.description: Crux is upper part of the groove.
content.protection: Small to Medium nuts or cams at bottom, 2 bolts on route about 20 ft up left of the seam and the 2nd 8ft higher right of the seam, then a nut or cam protects the crux moves above.
content.location: Right of Air Voyager, the right groove of the 2 grooves on the wall.

climbs.name: Bozo Buttress
climbs.fa: Galen Kirkwood and Mike Paul, September 1976

content.description: This is a good quality face climb.  It must be one of the easiest bolted faces in the park.
content.protection: 3 bolts plus gear for an anchor on top
content.location: This is at the upper left end of the face, left of the downclimb.  It is a very low angle slab.

climbs.name: Air Voyager
climbs.fa: Rob Mulligan and Bill Odenthal, March 1986

content.description: Crux is passing the first bolt, Rob ripped out an air voyager runner stopping just short of the gound on the FA.
content.protection: Bolt at bottom, small to medium pro above.
